The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 June is 42,809 (4,954.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 June, there were 277 new confirmed cases (32.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 June, there were 198 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 40% (79 extra cases).
